      • update

        public EncapsulatedPacket update(EncapsulatedPacket encapsulated)
                          throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
                                 java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Updates the data for the split packet while also verifying that the EncapsulatedPacket belongs to this split packet.
        Parameters:
        encapsulated - the encapsulated packet chunk.
        Returns:
        the packet if finished, null if data is still missing.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the encapsulated is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the encapsulated is not part of the bigger split packet based on whether or not it is split, its splitId, splitCount, or reliability, or if the splitIndex is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the splitCount of the encapsulated packet, or another encapsulated packet has been registered with the same splitIndex.
